 hopelessness, Numbered Days offers a powerful examination of the complex interplay of writing and mourning. And in these heartbreaking diaries, we see the first glimpses of a question that would haunt the twentieth century: Can such unimaginable horror be represented at all?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDiariesxHistory and criticism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)vPersonal narrativesxHistory and criticism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xHistoriography. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xPersonal narrativesxHistory and criticism. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945), in literature. 0aJewsxDiariesxHistory and criticism. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xPersonal narrativesxHistory and criticism. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300135039423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300135039.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles